    <item>
      <title>The Making of &#34;Infinite Summer&#34; (Part 1)</title>
      <link>https://www.jivarsound.com/blog/the-making-of-infinite-summer-part-1/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 20 Jun 2018 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <author>j.ivar.sound@gmail.com (Jason I. Aizkalns)</author>
      <guid>https://www.jivarsound.com/blog/the-making-of-infinite-summer-part-1/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;This song was supposed to be &lt;em&gt;very&lt;/em&gt; different.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It started when &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.facebook.com/steve.peiffer.1&#34; class=&#34;link light-blue hover-bg-lightest-blue hover-near-black&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noreferrer&#34;&gt;Steve Peiffer&lt;/a&gt; approached me to
come up with a summer banger &amp;ndash; something that he could release down at the shore.
We got together one night and&amp;hellip;failed&amp;hellip;we failed hard. What Steve wanted was&amp;hellip;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style=&#34;width:100%;height:0;padding-bottom:56%;position:relative;&#34;&gt;&lt;iframe src=&#34;https://giphy.com/embed/M3o6jPwh4jHGw&#34; style=&#34;width:100%; height:100%; position:absolute; border:0;&#34; class=&#34;giphy-embed&#34; allowFullScreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;hellip;but every chord progression and melody I kept writing was more&amp;hellip;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style=&#34;width:100%;height:0;padding-bottom:100%;position:relative;&#34;&gt;&lt;iframe src=&#34;https://giphy.com/embed/3o6fJ2YXyzU0bxxywg&#34; style=&#34;width:100%; height:100%; position:absolute; border:0;&#34; class=&#34;giphy-embed&#34; allowFullScreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We eventually called the session a bust and I left with some ideas and lyrics
from Steve:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure class=&#34;ba br3 b--near-white shadow mt3 center&#34;&gt;
  &lt;img src=&#34;https://www.jivarsound.com/images/posts/infinite-summer-verse.jpg&#34; class=&#34;w-100 measure br--top br3 db&#34; alt=&#39;Original lyrics by Steve Peiffer.&#39;&gt;
  &lt;figcaption class=&#34;f5 bg-near-white br--bottom br2 dark-gray i mv0 pv2 ph3&#34;&gt;Original lyrics by Steve Peiffer.&lt;/figcaption&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Refusing to give up and relying on some late night &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hypnagogia&#34; class=&#34;link light-blue hover-bg-lightest-blue hover-near-black&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noreferrer&#34;&gt;hypnagogic&lt;/a&gt;
creativity, I was finally getting somewhere and wrote a workable hook:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure class=&#34;ba br3 b--near-white shadow mt3 center&#34;&gt;
  &lt;img src=&#34;https://www.jivarsound.com/images/posts/infinite-summer-hook.jpg&#34; class=&#34;w-100 measure br--top br3 db&#34; alt=&#39;The hook for &amp;#34;Infinite Summer&amp;#34;.&#39;&gt;
  &lt;figcaption class=&#34;f5 bg-near-white br--bottom br2 dark-gray i mv0 pv2 ph3&#34;&gt;The hook for &amp;#34;Infinite Summer&amp;#34;.&lt;/figcaption&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I grabbed my iPhone, placed it on the table, and quickly recorded the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;audio class=&#34;js-player&#34; src=&#34;https://www.jivarsound.com/audio/making-of-infinite-summer/Infinite%20Summer%20%28Original%20Idea%29.mp3&#34;&gt;&lt;/audio&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While certainly not the club hit we were shooting for, this felt like it had potential.
The original song title, &amp;ldquo;Beaches and Bros&amp;rdquo; no longer felt appropriate and eventually
this would be renamed to &amp;ldquo;Infinite Summer&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The next day, the song progressed into a more workable demo:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;audio class=&#34;js-player&#34; src=&#34;https://www.jivarsound.com/audio/making-of-infinite-summer/Infinite%20Summer%20%28Scratch%20Demo%29.mp3&#34;&gt;&lt;/audio&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In time, I would tweak a few lyrical lines and wrote a second a verse to be sung
by a female. Stay tuned&amp;hellip;more to come on this one!&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
